.SH "NAME"
Pod::Weaver::Plugin::Transformer \- apply arbitrary transformers
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 4.015
.SH "OVERVIEW"
.IX Header "OVERVIEW"
This plugin acts as a Pod::Weaver::Role::Dialect that applies an arbitrary
Pod::Elemental::Transformer to your input document.  It is configured like
this:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&  [\-Transformer / Lists]
\&  transformer = List
\&  format_name = outline
.Ve
.PP
This will end up creating a transformer like this:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&  my $xform = Pod::Elemental::Transformer::List\->new({
\&    format_name => \*(Aqoutline\*(Aq,
\&  });
.Ve
.PP
and that transformer will then be handed the entire input Pod document.
